  • Uses of Item.Settings in net.minecraft.item

    Methods in net.minecraft.item that return Item.Settings
    Modifier and Type
    Method
    Description
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.fireproof()
    If called, any item with this Settings instance is immune to fire and lava damage.
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.food(FoodComponent foodComponent)
    When set, any item configured with this Settings instance will be edible based on the provided FoodComponent.
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.group(ItemGroup group)
    Sets the ItemGroup of any item using this Settings instance.
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.maxCount(int maxCount)
    Sets the maximum stack count of any ItemStack with an Item using this Settings instance.
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.maxDamage(int maxDamage)
    Sets the maximum durability of any item configured with this Settings instance.
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.maxDamageIfAbsent(int maxDamage)
    Calls maxDamage If this Settings instance has not already set max damage (or if max damage is the default value, 0).
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.rarity(Rarity rarity)
    Sets the Rarity of any item configured with this Settings instance, which changes the color of its name.
    Item.Settings
    Item.Settings.recipeRemainder(Item recipeRemainder)
    Sets the recipe remainder for any item configured with this Settings instance.
